See the full review @ <a href="http://www.coolhunting.com/tech/move-nude-audio-wireless-speakers.php">Coolhunting.com</a>

We loaned out our Chief Creative Office (Peter Riering-Czekalla) to spend the morning with Cool Hunting‚Äôs reporter Nara Shin. Read further to see some of the interview highlights and hear what she thought about the range.

The first quote from Peter starts with: "We don't believe that the world needs another premium speaker brand, but needs something that delivers good design: Simple, engaging, playful and personality without trying too hard‚Äîat a fair price. We want to be the countertrend to over-premiumization."

The article then leads on to say: NudeAudio achieves great sound quality at half the price by stripping away all of those "additional" features many consumer speakers boast‚Äîsuch as dual or stereo pairing, talk-back and alarm functions. "Simple design is the way of keeping the cost accessible. The only feature we added is the microphone so you can make phone calls‚Äîand so friends can join the call." Focusing on just the essential audio feature allowed NudeAudio to devote more funds to higher quality amplifiers and drivers for their speakers. They also avoid celebrity endorsements and large advertising campaigns as not to pass those costs onto the customer; instead, they rely mostly on word of mouth.

<a href="http://nudeaudio.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/NudeAudio_Cool-Hunting.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1493" alt="NudeAudio_Cool Hunting" src="http://nudeaudio.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/NudeAudio_Cool-Hunting.png" width="865" height="567" /></a>

We‚Äôre pleased to report that having used the speakers, Cool Hunting had some rather nice things to say about our bluetooth speakers <a href="http://nudeaudio.com/overview/">bluetooth speakers</a>. Here's their closing remarks:

‚ÄúOverall, the "Move" speakers are remarkably loud and crisp and even the smallest speaker packs a huge punch. They are charged and ready to go as soon as the box is opened; the battery lasts eight hours and is rechargeable with the provided USB charging cable. For outdoor use, we recommend the M, which had the strongest combination of portability and sound quality. For moving within the house, the larger L has full-range sound and doesn't clip, even when cranked all the way up.:";s:10:"post_title";s:52:"Cool Hunting 'Move' Speaker Range Review & Interview";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:46:"cool-hunting-portable-speaker-review-interview";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-11-01 11:57:05";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-11-01 11:57:05";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:28:"http://nudeaudio.com/?p=1491";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:1;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1562";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-02-04 15:43:37";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-02-04 15:43:37";s:12:"post_content";s:3755:"<div style="text-align: center;"><dl id="attachment_1560"><dt><a href="http://www.nudeaudio.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Studio-5-Bluetooth-Speaker.png"><img class="alignnone" alt="NudeAudio Studio 5  Bluetooth &amp; Lightning Speaker" src="http://www.nudeaudio.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Studio-5-Bluetooth-Speaker.png" width="658" height="559" /></a></dt><dd>NudeAudio Studio 5 - ¬†Bluetooth &amp; Lightning Speaker</dd></dl></div>
&nbsp;

<b>4<sup>th</sup>¬†February, San Francisco</b>. We're delighted to announce our first home speaker - Studio 5. ¬†Breaking the mould of traditional speaker design, the iconic looking, asymmetric speaker features both Bluetooth and an Apple Lightning connector, making it compatible with all smartphones and tablets. The home speaker houses a powerful 2.1 system capable of delivering rich, crisp, high fidelity sound.

Tom Old Co-Founder enthused ‚ÄúStudio 5 is very different to other home speakers in the market. We‚Äôve really spent time considering how and where the speaker is going to be used. People don‚Äôt just want a speaker to sound good, they‚Äôre asking for a speaker that compliments the aesthetics of their home interior too. Gone are the days of design-conscious consumers accepting a black plastic box into their home.‚Äù

Studio 5 has been designed to compliment a chic, contemporary home interior. Real metal elements accompany fabric and soft touch paint on the asymmetric housing; creating a refined, yet bold form. The play-control buttons are subtly hidden in the circular dock-plate and the device support is made of transparent polycarbonate.

While the colour pallet is quiet, the acoustics are anything but. The 3 inch subwoofer and two high-fidelity neodymium-drivers work in perfect harmony to deliver a high-resolution sound that stretches from 70Hz ~ 18kHz. Three pre-set bass settings allow users to beef up or down the speaker according to the genre of music and personal taste.

<b>¬†</b>The speaker provides a variety of connection options. For the latest iPhone and iPod variants, you can play and charge with an Apple Lightning connector. Along with aux-in, the speaker also features a CSR Bluetooth chipset, which provides a quick and reliable Bluetooth connection. Impressively, Dual-pairing over Bluetooth is possible enabling two devices to be connected at the same time - music can then be switched between devices by simply pressing pause and play.

For the technically savvy, NudeAudio has also included AptX (Advanced Digital Signal Processing) coding technology. When using the NudeAudio Studio 5 with other AptX compatible devices (e.g. any Mac with OSX or Samsung Galaxy S4 Smartphones or newer), the audio is CD quality and indistinguishable to a wired source.

Studio 5 is available today at $179.99 / ‚Ç¨149.99 / ¬£149.99 and can be bought from Grand Street (<a href="https://grandst.com/p/studio5">https://grandst.com/p/studio5</a>), John Lewis (in the UK) and Amazon. Further design, homeware and consumer electronics stores will be announced in the coming months.

Key Spec:
